.SH NAME
XRInputSource.gamepad \- XRInputSource: gamepad property
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Secure context:\f[R] This feature is available only in secure
contexts (HTTPS).
.PP
The read\-only \f[CR]XRInputSource\f[R] property
\f[B]\f[CB]gamepad\f[B]\f[R] returns a \f[CR]Gamepad\f[R] object
describing the state of the buttons and axes on the XR input source, if
it is a gamepad or comparable device.
If the device isn\[cq]t a gamepad\-like device, this property\[cq]s
value is \f[CR]null\f[R].
.PP
The \f[CR]Gamepad\f[R] instance returned behaves as described by the
Gamepad API.
However, there are a few things to note:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]Gamepad\f[R] instances belonging to \f[CR]XRInputSource\f[R] are
not included in the array returned by
\f[CR]navigator.getGamepads()\f[R].
Gamepads are strictly associated with the WebXR hardware and are not
general\-purpose gaming devices.
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]Gamepad.id\f[R] is an empty string (\f[CR]\[dq]\[dq]\f[R])
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]Gamepad.index\f[R] is \f[CR]\-1\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]Gamepad.connected\f[R] is \f[CR]true\f[R] until the
\f[CR]XRInputSource\f[R] is removed from the list of active XR input
sources or the \f[CR]XRSession\f[R] is ended.
.IP \[bu] 2
If an axis reported by \f[CR]Gamepad.axes\f[R] represents an axis of a
touchpad, the value is 0 when the associated
\f[CR]GamepadButton.touched\f[R] property is \f[CR]false\f[R].
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]Gamepad.mapping\f[R] returns \[lq]xr\-standard\[rq].
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using a gamepad input source
.IP
.EX
\f[B]for\f[R] (\f[B]const\f[R] source \f[B]of\f[R] frame.session.inputSources) {
  \f[B]const\f[R] gamepad = source.gamepad;
  \f[B]if\f[R] (gamepad) {
    \f[B]if\f[R] (gamepad.buttons[2].pressed) {
      \f[I]// do something\f[R]
    }
  }
}
